events.data: Hello I am interested in buying.
Great!  I am listing this at 2250
I'm going to be honest with you, I am very very limited by my budget... I hope we can negotiate a fair price...
I understand.  However, this apartment has a lot of amenities that you may like.  It's clean, large, and close to the bay.  In fact, you can see the bay from the apartment
That sounds great. That countertop looks very outdated. I am stuck at 1350 but if the countertop was updated I could probably go much higher...
Well, we are not finished updating just yet.We still have to do the kitchen.  It's available on July 1st so we still have some time to replace it.  What's the highest you think you could go?
I think 1750 would be fair with a new countertop.

I really couldn't let it go for less than the 2250 asking price.  I am remodeling more than just the counter.  New carpet, new appliances, freshly painted and I put in an energy efficient HVAC so your utility bills will be lower.
That all sounds great but like I said I am limited by a very very low budget. I can forego the new countertop though if it means a fairer price.
How would you feel if I waived the first month's rent, but you have to agree to a 12 month lease?
I can't go any higher than 1750 and I didn't think you were coming back so I submitted it as my final offer.
I think with this location and the remodel's I'm putting in to it, I can't go 500 lower, so I'll have to reject your offer. Thank you for your interest, though.
Thanks for considering it. Have a good night.

events.data: What are campy record parts? Is that the brand of the parts?
Well, let me tell you, campy means Campagnolo, but as you're interested in this fine bicycle I'm sure you're already familiar with that.

Ah, yes I am a fine connasuer of bikes! I notice that the wheel size for this bike is difficult to come by these days and also that brakes tend to wear over time, even when not in use. So I am prepared to offer you 1400 for the bicycle. How does that sound?
Oh, friend, this is a fine machine, I couldn't take only $1400 for it. It's a steal at $2000!
Since it's in mint condition, how about 1600? It will take me quite a while to find fresh treads for these wheels!
Well, we're getting closer, but I'm afraid $1600 is still too low. Would you be willing to come pick the bike up?
Yes, I can drive to you and pick it up myself.
Okay, if you're willing to come pick the bike up tonight, I'd be willing to let it go for $1750. I'm afraid that's my best price.
Deal.

Description: Open House: Sunday 12pm-2pm

This 1Br/1Ba apartment is on the ground floor of a beautiful turn-of-the-century Edwardian Manor with all the architectural details, grand foyers and stairwells indicative of the style. item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special

Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)
Lightweight Columbus SL tubing throughout frame and forks.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.

item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special

Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)
Lightweight Columbus SL tubing throughout frame and forks.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.
item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special

events.data: I love this bike!! How much are you asking?
Hello.
It's listed at only $650
Hmm, I am desperate and your bike is the only one listed near me. I really cant do anything over 400
This is a vintage Marcello Faggin, I couldn't let it go for only $400. Frankly, in this condition it would be a steal at twice the list price.
Yes, but you need it gone correct. Probably just sitting there collecting dust. How about $550. Knock 100 bucks off for a girl!

Well, just consider the 6x2 drivetrain. In good condition those alone go for about $200 in some circles. It really is a fair price at $650, in a bike shop a used Faggin in this condition could go for $900 easily.
Okay, great, I'm glad we could make a deal :)

events.data: I love the Sofa!  How long have you had it?
I bought it in March of last year, so a bit longer than one year.

I think I could live with $285.  It's a deal!

item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special

Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)
Lightweight Columbus SL tubing throughout frame and forks.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.
item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special

Hi, I am interested in your piano. Will you take $50 for it? I want it for my daughter.
$50 is quite a bit lower than I was wanting to sell this piano for, it is a really great piano. I can offer it for $90, but I will make sure the piano gets tuned before you pick it up.

I think that's a deal. Can I come look at it first though?

events.data: Hi so I have a great closet organizer for just under $500. Do you have any questions?
Are you the original owner? Is this the actual picture of your item? Are there any dings, dents, chips in paint? Thanks for initiating convo!
Yes, I am the only owner. It was well taken care of. The item of the photo is indeed mine. There's no chips, dents or dings.  You have to pick it up.
Okay. Is this heavy? Will you be available to help load?
No, my backs bad, you have to lift it yourself. Please have cash when you get here. My little niece can help you get it in your vehicle.
I can't go $499. Can you do $300, since I am meeting you and loading myself?
Absolutely not, this is a designer closet rack. The lowest I could go is $420.
Elfa sounds like Ikea to me. I would hardly call it designer. $410
Meet me in the middle at $415 and you have to disassemble it.
It needs to disassembled before I get there. If I have to disassemble, I must go back and insist on $400
It's not worth my time to disassemble it for $15. You can do it when you get here.
Then I need a deeper discount. Disassembling is part of your job as the owner, especially if you want this gone.
You just said you'd do $400.
I am sorry, I misread that. I will take it for 400, I pack up and disassemble. We have a deal?
I don't know, is there anything else you can do for me?
I am disassembling and picking up, plus giving you $400. I think that is a hell of  deal on your part

Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)
Lightweight Columbus SL tubing throughout frame and forks.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.

Description: Open House: Sunday 12pm-2pm

This 1Br/1Ba apartment is on the ground floor of a beautiful turn-of-the-century Edwardian Manor with all the architectural details, grand foyers and stairwells indicative of the style. This apartment gets plenty of sunlight all day, has lots of ample closet space, a separate living room, bathroom with claw-foot tub and hardwood floors.

events.data: Hey! I am very interested in the mattress. Would you say it is more on the firm or soft side?
Hey there, thanks for contacting me. I'd say it's more on the soft side. It has a plush pillow top.
Awesome, I definitely prefer soft. Does it come with any sort of warranty?
I did originally purchase it with a warranty.  It was a 5 year warranty, so there's a year and a half left.
Makes sense. Does this include a boxspring as well?
Oh yes. The boxspring is free.
What a deal! If I were to pick it up, would you be willing to take $130?
How about 135 because of the added warranty?
That sounds good to me! $135 it is.
Great.  Contact me at 345-7878 when you're ready to pick it up.

events.data: Hey so I'm interested in the closet rack, can you tell me about it?
Sure! It's very sturdy and does not need to be attached to the wall as it has freestanding feet. It's 10feet wide with 12" and 16" deep shelves. All together it's 83" tall
How's the condition, is it nice?
Yes, it's in excellent condition, no rust or bending anywhere. Perfect for a library!
Is it already disassembled, or do I have to do that?
It's assembled and will fit in most pickup trucks, but if you need to dissasemble it, it's super easy to put back together.
Ok, but I'm looking to pay more towards $225 if I have to pick it up and do all of that myself. It looks huge.
That's a little too low.. can we do $275 and I'll help you move it?
I think you'd need to do most of the work for that price, you could consider the extra $50 a delivery fee.
You have a really good point there. Alright, I'll do $225

events.data: OMG
Hi! Are you interested in mt sofa?
Oh yes dear, my boyfriend and I loooooooove Lee Sofas

Well sure only $600 if your rich and gay, which I'm not, well one of those ! LOL
Ha! If you want, I can deliver for free.
Hmz, well we are worried about if you had a cat or dog, I'm mean it's not a big deal, but...
Nope. I have no pets.
Have you ever had it cleaned? By a professional, honey?
No, but it's been kept clean, and it's only about a year old
Ok, but you know we are all a little dirty, especially on the loveseat, or do you have kids in your place. I'm sorry, maybe this is a wholesome set of furniture...
It's quite wholesome. How much are you willing to pay?
Well, since you said it's clean, and you'll deliver, and it's practically BRAND neeew, we'll give you $420, and no we are straightedge, ha!
How about $500? It's really in great shape. No kids.
Only if you go on a date with us honey, never negotiate with a gay man, $400.
$450 is as low as I can go.
Oh I can't believe that, you gotta give me a reason, why are your credit cards so high? Ok, $420, that's high enough...
I recently divorced, and I can't afford to be charitable. I'm sure there's SOMEONE who could pay $450.

Oh, it's not that I can't pay you $450, but like I said we aren't rich. So we are willing to pay a fair price. Really any material object is only worth 1/3 of the price of the list, especially after it's been used by any other person. Therefore, technically, and reasonably I could only give you $200 in order for me to not be a foolish capitalist. So, giving you even $420 with good humor is still way too much. So I'll double the reasonable offer a strong capitalist knows it is worth and give you $400. You need it, you have to pay the divorcee.

events.data: hello
Hey, so you were thinking about a BMW?
yes, i am very interested.
Oh, well that's cool. Usually people see me and lowball me, I am obviously a gay surfer.
oh why would they do that? thats not fair

Well, surfers live in their cars in the search for the right wave, so this thing has some wear and tear. But, listen, I have to drive all over the place to get the best wave. So, you know I pay the best mechanics. I don't know anything about mechanical engineering.
oh ok. i understand . that is awesome. you are one lucky guy!

Sometimes, and this car has brought me lots of luck in the search. But, listen, I don't want you to think I'm a thief, I might be a pirate, but not a thief! LOL, really, Carfax is gonna tell you some mileage difference, it's because I bought a new engine off my Bulgarian mechanic. He trained on the BMW race team in Germany, look him up, stupid expensive. But this car will certainly get you where you need to go, and is the best BMW wagon on any US coast.
Lol! that is very important. i want a car that get me anywhere i need to go. This is a nice car; however, you are asking for too much. you know, it is not a brand new BMW.

Totally, it is super used, like I said. But that is why I have it listed so high. It was a long time ago, and I bought it for $35,000, so I figured I would just cut a zero off. Still, though it is used. I'll five it to you for less than 10% of it's original tag, I'll GIVE you this ride, for $3000. But, you may have to sell it back to me in a year. No, no, just kidding.
LOL. come on! the price is still high. i will give you $1750 right now for the car. i am ready to take it home with me right at this moment!

Ha, ok. It is high. But I'm not. How did you come up with 1750? You must be tired. Listen, you can sleep in the back. I have many a time. I'll even give you my old Yoga mat. Ok, ok, $2999, lets do this!

i know that you are not high! well, i am a young broke college student. i was able to save some of my financial aid money in order to buy this very nice car. i really need it. Do you know how many times i have to ask people for rides. This is a great opportunity for me to buy a car. i am willing to pay $1800.

events.data: Hi, is your truck still for sale?
Yes it is!
how many miles?
It is actually pretty low mileage, my grandmother only drove it to church on Sundays.  Church wasn't very far, so it only has 15,000 miles on it.  Such a deal!
pretty cool grandma to be riding in a tacoma

Yeah, I come from a long line of rabble-rousers!  We originally got it for her for her rabbit farm, but she kept bring the bunnies in the house and not selling them.  Did you need a bunny with the truck?
I don't need a bunny but is your grandma single? How about I take her out for a nice steak dinner and give you $4400 for the truck?

Sorry, Grandma is a vegetarian and she needs more than that.  She just received her medical marijuana farming license and there are a lot of start up costs.  Although, you can become one of her "special" customers and get a deal on the new crop.  Grandma can grow anything.  (We are still recovering from the zucchini incident).
Would you accept $5000 and I'll give her 100 Sensi Star clones

As the bunnies multiplied like, well, bunnies, sadly, we don't have quite enough room for the clones.  If Grandma throws in the medical license, two bunnies (they are trained in the art of self defense and would make excellent body guards (one of the reasons we had difficulty selling them for meat).  Also, the price the train car and the hydroponic system is quite high.  $5000 doesn't cover it.  Oh did I mention that the truck has a hot tub in the back?

Description: Selling to finance my trip to continue the Standing Rock #NoDAPL movement.
55cm size frame Triathlon bike late 80's.

This may be one of the best Japanese engineered bikes ever produced. Aluminum frames are notorious for passing the road vibrations to the rider, causing additional fatigue. events.data: Hello, are you interested in the car I have available?
Hello, yes I am interested.
Great, do you have any questions? I'm asking $4,000.

The scratches are really fine and not noticeable to anyone passing by. You would have to inspect the car closely to reveal them.
How is the motor? How many miles?

Car will be sold as is. What about $3,700?
How about 2000?
A little low for what I'm needing. $3,300
The miles is high how about 2500?
I'll meet you at $3,000. That would be my lowest.
Do you have receipts for all the parts you have replaced?
Yes
Ok I can do 3000 because I can see that you have done a lot of work to it.

This may be one of the best Japanese engineered bikes ever produced. Aluminum frames are notorious for passing the road vibrations to the rider, causing additional fatigue. item.Title: Nishiki Altron 7000 (late 80s triathlon)

events.data: Hi :-) what kind of shape is this in?
It's still in very good shape. I've only used it for basic road riding. No competitions or anything too intense.
Nice :-) so no rusty bits or problems with chains or gears? I like why your're selling it, btw
Thanks. Yeah, no mechanical issues or worn out parts. It was a classic design, and I did my best to take care of it.
I understand they have different sizes for these bikes? I'm on the short side, would it work for me?
It's a 55 cm frame, which is designed for people 5'6" to 5'9", but of course you can adjust the handlebar and seat height to your preferences.
Perfect, sorry about the dumb question. Its listed for 600, but I only have a budget of 400, could that work?
I think I could probably go $500. Would that work?
It's for such a good cause, I can't go as high as five though (I'm sorry) but I do have my mad money :-) It's not much, but I can get together 450...
I think that'll work for me. You seem like you're going to give it a great home.
I'll try :-) thanks!

Hi

events.data: Hello!
Hello, is the apartment still available?
Yes, it is. Would you like to see it?
Before I see it, I have a few questions. Are any utilities included in the rent. $10995 is a bit much and are pets allowed?

No, utilities are not included, and small pets are allowed with a pet deposit. Keep in mind that you could have 18 or more people sharing the rent, depending on how you furnish the bedrooms, so that brings down the per-person price a lot!

Yeah, more people equals less per person, but I don't want too big a crowd. Some people just aren't clean. How about we start out at $5000 for 5 people and renegotiate later if I need to bring more people in?
That's less than half price! My boss would kill me! I can't go lower than $8000. How many people you share with is up to you.
Okay, I'm just trying to save you the eviction process if we can't pay. I think I can find 3 more people and get you $8000 but we'll need water and gas covered.
I could do that.

item.Title: Beautiful Cherry Wood Mirror from Cherry Tree Design

events.data: Hello, I was interested in purchasing your cherry wood mirror.
Great. It is very beautiful mirror.
I see you are asking $160. Does it have any scratches or anything? I see it is used.
It does not have any scratches on the wood There is a small imperfection on the mirror. It is very small about the size of a sharpee tip. It isn't noticable I just wanted to make sure you knew.
Could I perhaps pick it up in the morning for $140?
That is fair if you will be picking up. I will only accept cash is that okay?
That would be perfect, Thank you.

events.data: Hello.
Hello is the apartment still available?
Yes it is. I am surprised that it is. It is an amazing 6 bedroom apt
How would you rate the safety of the neighborhood?
On a scale of 1-10. I find it is a 10. They are no issues in this area.
When would I be able to move in?
You will be able to move in Aug. 1st.
What floor is the apartment on?
The first floor.
Is cable included in the rent?
Yes, Cable and DSL are included.
OK I'm interested but it's a little out of my price range.   Could you do 7000?
I could do that. Do you have anymore questions about the apt? You can come in the morning to fill out paperwork.
I will be there in the morning.  THank you!
You are welcome.

events.data: Hello im very interested in your springy chairs. Why are you selling them? Are they in good condition?
Hi, I am going to be moving in a couple weeks, They are in decent shape. The weather over the years have gotten to them a bit. Nothing a tiny bit of TLC couldn't fix up though.
How about the cushions? Are they in good shape? Do they have any smell?
They have been cleaned. They are in good shape. I am asking $50 for the pair. Ive washed everything all up. Its mostly just the sun that has gotten to them a bit.
Ok well how about 45 for them and I can pick them up?
45 seems fair. Could you bring cash? That would be great.
